        <h1>LeetCode 1513: Number of Substrings With Only 1s (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given a binary string s, return the number of substrings with all characters 1's. Since the answer may be too large, return it modulo 10^9 + 7.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: s = "0110111"<br>
                Output: 9<br>
                Explanation: There are 9 substrings in total with only 1's characters. "1" → 5 times, "11" → 3 times, "111" → 1 time.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int numSub(string s) {
        const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;
        long long result = 0;
        int count = 0;
        
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c == '1') {
                // Increment count of consecutive 1s
                count++;
                // Add count to result (number of new substrings ending here)
                result = (result + count) % MOD;
            } else {
                // Reset count when we encounter 0
                count = 0;
            }
        }
        
        return result;
    }
};</code></pre>
